ty of early Judaism—the Bible, post-biblical texts, and even classical rabbinic literature. The greatest development over time is only that the boundaries between God and gods become at once clearer and less rigid.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aGod (Judaism) 0aGod (Judaism). 0aJudaismxHistoryyPost-exilic period, 586 B.C.-210 A.D. 0aJudaismxHistoryyTo 70 A.D. 4aGeneral. 4aJudaism. 4aReligion. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertGorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074330240uhttps://doi.org/10.31826/978146324334040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781463243340423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781463243340/original  a978-3-11-074330-2  Gorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074335-7  DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK